Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Kenya Airways, Kakuzi Shares Move

-- B y   J o h n s t o n e   O l e   T u r a n a
-- 
2011-02-17T17:31:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-kenya-airways-kakuzi-shares-move.html
The Nigerian Stock Exchange All-
Share Index snapped two days of declines, advancing 0.6 percent
to 26,627.29 by the 2:30 p.m. close in Lagos, according to the
bourse.  Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index fell for a second day, slumping
0.3 percent to 2,066.14 at the 1:30 p.m. close of trading in  Port Louis . Kenya’s All-Share Index climbed 0.1 percent to 78.20
by the 3 p.m. close in Nairobi. Namibia’s FTSE  Namibia Overall
Index  slid for a third day, dropping 0.1 percent to 913.38 by
the 5 p.m. close of trading in Windhoek. The Ghana Stock
Exchange Composite Index fell 0.1 percent to 1,049.13 at the 3
p.m. close in Accra.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.    Kenya Airways Ltd . (KNAL KN) fell for a fourth day,
slipping 0.6 percent to 40.25 shillings. Sub-Saharan Africa’s
third-biggest carrier plans to raise capital for investment and
has hired CFC Stanbic Holdings Ltd. as an adviser, the company
said in a statement e-mailed late yesterday.    Kakuzi  Ltd. (KKZI KN), a Kenyan tea and fruit producer,
decreased for a third day this week on bets dry weather will
hurt production. The country may have dry weather until April
that could reduce farming output, according to the Kenya
Metrological Department. The stock slid as much as 1.9 percent
and traded down 0.6 percent to 79 shillings.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Johnstone Ole Turana in Nairobi at 
 jturana@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
